> The new entity would control reportedly 25% of the U.S. book market. This
> will probably intensify the winner-take-all trends that have been growing
> in publishing lately. I'm guessing author advances will go down, especially
> for the midlist authors -- the fewer bidding entities there are, the less
> motivation to outbid the other guy.
